Description: Negi, the boy wizard, learns he will be teaching English at an all-girls high school in Japan, but he must keep his powers a secret.
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 32
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts) and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 2
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: The backstory is complicated, but the gist is this: four 15-year-old male friends must turn an outcast wallflower into a lovely lady.
Title: THE WALLFLOWER, VOL. 27
Author: Tomoko Hayakawa

Description: Following in the footsteps of Sailor Moon, 13-year-old Minako Aino transforms into Sailor V. to protect the earth.
Title: CODENAME: SAILOR, VOL. 2
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: The incredibly popular manga series that spawned an anime series, stage musicals and countless imitators gets a new printing.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Cross Academy has day and evening students, but the latter have a secret: they are vampires.
Title: VAMPIRE KNIGHT, VOL. 13
Author: Matsuri Hino

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy.
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 11
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: This is a manga adaptation of the best selling childrenâ€™s series about ordinary housecats trying to fulfill extraordinary destinies.
Title: WARRIORS: BEYOND THE CODE, VOL. 2
Author: Erin Hunter

Description: A predecessor to "Sailor Moon," this collection of stories has never before been printed in the United States.
Title: CODENAME: SAILOR V, Vol. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human? In this volume: children are missing and Queen Victoria is not happy.
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 7
Author: Yana Toboso
